    "permission-bubbling": {
      "status": "active",
      "description": "Fixes critical permission issues: (1) Permission requests from subagents bubble to parent, (2) Each agent uses its OWN task permissions config (not parent's) - child config is authoritative for what that agent can delegate, (3) ctx.ask() bypass prevented - explicit agent config checked BEFORE user prompts so Always Allow cannot override agent deny rules, (4) Prevents delegation bypass attacks where agents spawn unauthorized subagents.",
      "issue": "https://github.com/randomm/opencode/issues/187",
